COME BE A PART OF OUR CREATIVE TEAM.\n\nJOB POSTING INFORMATION:\n\nThe Henegar Center in Melbourne Florida is looking for talented and professional candidates that are passionate about the arts and have a love for theatre. A fully equal opportunity employer, the Henegar looks for skilled artisans to help tell our stories and create magical worlds for our guests through our Mainstage, Blackbox, Special Event and Student Productions. We are hiring for several specific roles and always accepting resumes and portfolios to continually increase our talent pull of contracted designers. Learn more about our theatre, our mission, and production photos on our website at www.henegarcenter.com. \n\nInterested candidates should submit their Resume and or portfolio, or any profession links to our recruitment email auditions\u0040henegar.org . Our Team will review all interested candidates. Once information is collected, they will reach out directly if it is necessary to schedule an in-person interview or zoom call for those submitting outside of Florida. Please note not everyone who submits interest will receive an interview slot, however once we have completed our hiring process, all that submitted will be notified at that time. \n\nFull & Part time Salaried and Hourly Roles: We are seeking the following roles. Below we have listed if the role is full time\/part time\/ contracted\/or seasonal, with basic salary ranges and benefits. Additional details will be discussed for those with a scheduled in person interview \n\nFull time Salaried Scenic builders-\n\u00b7      Available start date after June 1st\n\u00b7      Salary range $42,000- $46,000\n\u00b7      Additional Benefits including paid time off (vacation \/sick), Health Insurance contribution, eligible holiday bonus.\n\u00b7      Top level roles & responsibilities include; Experience construction of Theatrical sets. Use of basic power tools. Working with a range of materials including lauan, foam, lumber, and plaster. Scenic painting. Trim and accent details. Mounting and rigging fly rails and scenic drops. Ability to carry heavy objects (up to 50 pounds) and use lift to heights over 10 feet. Order materials and maintain inventory. Assist with wiring electrical elements. Work under the Shop Foreman to achieve build completion by specific deadlines. Other duties as assigned and to be discussed further at interview. \n\nSeason Year Long Salaried Production Paid Internship-\n\u00b7      Available start date after June 1st\n\u00b7      Salary range $32,000- $35,000\n\u00b7      Additional Benefits including paid time off (vacation \/sick), Health Insurance contribution, eligible holiday bonus. Potential onsite housing and utilities included.\n\u00b7      Top level roles & responsibilities include; Directly supporting the Artistic and Associate Artistic Directors, Guest Directors and Contracted Creative Team. Rehearsal Manager to include set up and assistance of Auditions, Casting, Rehearsal Schedule, Social Media post creation, Creative meeting notes, staging notes, use of Microsoft office and Google sheets, Assist Director directly in logging and updating prop lists, furniture lists, sound and lighting notes, special orders for each production. Printing materials. Order and set up\/strike of catering. Office administrative tasks. Supporting the entire Team to achieve a successful production delivered by deadlines. \n\u00b7      Ability to work nights and weekends for rehearsals and some show weekends. \n\nSeason Year Long Salaried Shop\/Build\/Tech Paid Internship-\n\u00b7      Available start date after June 1st\n\u00b7      Salary range $32,000- $35,000\n\u00b7      Additional Benefits including paid time off (vacation \/sick), Health Insurance contribution, eligible holiday bonus. Potential onsite housing and utilities included.\n\u00b7      Top level roles & responsibilities include; Experience construction of Theatrical sets. Use of basic power tools. Working with a range of materials including lauan, foam, lumber, and plaster. Scenic painting. Trim and accent details. Mounting and rigging fly rails and scenic drops. Ability to carry heavy objects (up to 50 pounds) and use lift to heights over 10 feet. Order materials and maintain inventory. Assist with wiring electrical elements. Assist Lighting Designers, Sound Designers, Technical Director. Maintain a clean and safe backstage area. Work under the Shop Foreman to achieve build completion by specific deadlines. Other duties as assigned and discussed further at the interview.\n\nPart Time Hourly Box Office & Front of House Associate-\n\u00b7      Available start date after June 1st\n\u00b7      Hourly rate range $18- $20 an hour, approx. 20 hours per week\n\u00b7      Additional Benefits including paid time off (vacation \/sick), eligible holiday bonus.\n\u00b7      Top level roles & responsibilities include; Coverage of the Box Office during business hours. Answering phones and manning the ticketing window. Superior Guest service. Processing ticket sales, renewals, Memberships, seat moves. Assist with inventory of front of house materials. Keeping the Front of House clean and organized. Printing programs. Receiving shipments and distributing to other areas of business. Assist with set up and strike of special events. Assist with Management of Front of House when the House Manager is absent. Coverage of Front of House duties for Feller student programs and Blackbox special events. \n\u00b7      While most Box office coverage falls during the week, during the day from 9:30-6:30, candidates must have some evening and weekend availability. \n\u00b7      Other duties as assigned and discussed further at the interview. \n\nContracted Roles Show by Show:\n\nContracted Production Lighting Designer & Board Operators\n\n\u00b7      Please provide a resume, link to portfolio or other online examples of your work\n\u00b7      Please include any dates of availability or specific show interest\n\nContracted Production Sound Designer & Board Operators \n\n\u00b7      Please provide a resume, link to portfolio or other online examples of your work\n\u00b7      Please include any dates of availability or specific show interest\n\nContracted Feller Student Programs Rehearsal\/Stage Manager \n\n\u00b7      Please provide a resume, link to portfolio or other online examples of your work\n\u00b7      Please include any dates of availability or specific show interest\n\u00b7      Available start date after June 1st\n\u00b7      Contract based on specific show needs varies from $550- $1,200 stipend \n\u00b7      Top level roles & responsibilities include; Directly supporting the Education Director, the Associate Artistic Director, and Guest Directors and Contracted Creative Team. \nMust work well with children ranging from Kindergarten through High School. Rehearsal Manager to include set up and assistance of Auditions, Casting, Rehearsal Schedule, Social Media post creation, Creative meeting notes, staging notes, use of Microsoft office and Google sheets, Assist Director directly in logging and updating prop lists, furniture lists, sound and lighting notes, special orders for each production. Pulling or purchasing costumes for all students. Printing materials. Order and set up\/strike. Office administrative tasks. Supporting the entire Team to achieve a successful production delivered by deadlines. Sewing and alterations are a plus.
